variable.notes:
The Bloomreach basket contains detailed conversion parameters for each product that was purchased. This parameter is a JavaScript dictionary that contains one key called "items" with the value of the key being the list of products purchased.

Variable Type: Array of Objects

Format: 
 'basket': {
   "items": [
        {
          "prod_id" : "{{Product ID}}",
          "sku": "{{SKU}}",.
          "name": "{{Product Name}}",
          "quantity": "{{Quantity}}",
          "price": "{{Price}}"
        },
        {
          "prod_id" : "{{Product ID}}",
          "sku": "{{SKU}}",
          "name": "{{Product Name}}",
          "quantity": "{{Quantity}}",
          "price": "{{Price}}"
        }
      ]
    };


(1) Basket Example with 1 product:
 'basket': {
    'items': [
        {
          'prod_id' : 'pid123456',  // this is the product ID and needs to match the product ID sent in the feed.
          'sku' : 'sku789', // This is the sku id. This should match the unique sku id sent in the feed. It only applies if you have skus. 
          'name': 'Cashmere Sweater', // product name
          'quantity': '1', // quantity of this product in the basket
          'price': '65.95', // This should be the unit price per product and NOT the total price. If the item is on sale, this is the unit sale price.
          'prod_ver': '12345-789', // This only applies to B2B customers. Leave empty if not this a B2B implementation.
       }
    ]
 };

(2) Basket Example with 2 products, first product has a sku, second product does not have a sku:
 'basket': {
   "items": [
        {
          "prod_id" : "pid123456",
          "sku": "sku789",.
          "name": "Cashmere Sweater",
          "quantity": "1",
          "price": "65.95"
        }, // make sure to add a comma delimiter to separate multiple product
        {
          "prod_id" : "pid56789",
          "sku": "",
          "name": "Blue Skinny Jeans",
          "quantity": "2",
          "price": "79.99"
        } // no comma delimiter after the last product
      ]
   };

(3) Basket Example with 2 products, first product is a Product Bundle, second product is an individual product:
'basket': {
   "items": [
        {
          "prod_id" : "bundle223344",
          "sku": "",.
          "name": "Linen Bed Sheet Set",
          "quantity": "1",
          "price": "265.95"
        }, // make sure to add a comma delimiter to separate multiple product
        {
          "prod_id" : "pid56789",
          "sku": "",
          "name": "Blue Skinny Jeans",
          "quantity": "2",
          "price": "79.99"
        } // no comma delimiter after the last product
      ]
   };


If the item in the basket is a Product Collection, Product Bundle or Sku Set:
         (a)  Your Collection Pages have their own unique ID and are sold exactly like standalone products, then enter the collection ID in the prod_id 
                field. Make sure that this collection ID is sent in the feed in the product ID field.

         (b) Your Product Collections have their own unique ID, but cannot be purchased as a whole; only the collections' individual parts/products 
               can be purchased and each of these individual parts have their own ID. In this case, list all individual products in the basket and the 
               prod_id is the the ID of each product. Make sure that each product ID is sent in the feed in the product ID field.

         (c) Products that are a part of a Collection but can only be purchased from their own individual product page. In this case follow the same 
               guideline as described in (b)



Basket Format after Conversion Pixel fires:
i<prod_id>'s<sku>'n<product_name>'q<quantity>'p<price>'r<prod_ver>
Each product parameter will be separated by '
Each product will be separated by !

Based on the Basket Example (1) above, the basket will show the following string after the pixel has fired:
!ipid123456'ssku789'nCashmere Sweater'q1.0'p69.95'r12345-789

Based on Basket Example (2) above, the basket will show the following string after the pixel has fired:
!ipid123456'ssku789'nCashmere Sweater'q1.0'p69.95'r12345-789!ipid56789'nBlue Skinny Jeans'q2.0'p79.99
If the sku or prod_ver is left empty, it will not show in the transformed basket string.

Based on the Basket Example (3) above, the basket will show the following string after the pixel has fired:
!bundle223344'nLinen Bed Sheet Set'q1.0'p265.95!ipid56789'nBlue Skinny Jeans'q2.0'p79.99

